          <h2>The Overdose Crisis in Arizona</h2>
          <p>Arizona faces a devastating overdose crisis that disproportionately affects communities impacted by incarceration and the criminal legal system. Our Drug Policy & Overdose Prevention program works at the intersection of public health, harm reduction, and systemic reform.</p>
          
          <p>We address the challenges of substance use through evidence-based strategies that save lives while advocating for policy changes that treat addiction as a health issue, not a criminal one.</p>
          
          <h2>Harm Reduction Services</h2>
          <h3>Naloxone Distribution & Training</h3>
          <p>We provide naloxone (Narcan) distribution and training to:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Currently and formerly incarcerated individuals</li>
            <li>Family members and loved ones</li>
            <li>Community organizations and service providers</li>
            <li>Prison reentry programs</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Overdose Prevention Education</h3>
          <p>Our team conducts community trainings on:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Recognizing overdose signs and symptoms</li>
            <li>Administering naloxone effectively</li>
            <li>Good Samaritan laws and legal protections</li>
            <li>Linking to treatment and support services</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Systems Change Advocacy</h2>
          <h3>Treatment Access in Carceral Settings</h3>
          <p>We advocate for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Medication-Assisted Treatment (MAT) in prisons and jails</li>
            <li>Continuity of care upon release</li>
            <li>Evidence-based substance use programs</li>
            <li>Peer support specialist training for returning citizens</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h3>Drug Policy Reform</h3>
          <p>Our legislative priorities include:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Good Samaritan law expansion</li>
            <li>Decriminalization of fentanyl test strips</li>
            <li>Needle exchange program authorization</li>
            <li>Treatment diversion programs</li>
            <li>Sentencing reform for drug-related offenses</li>
          </ul>
          
          <h2>Family Preservation</h2>
          <p>Substance use disorders affect entire families, especially during pregnancy. We work to ensure pathways to freedom and return are wide and unobstructed, including support for individuals with substance use disorders during childbirth.</p>
          
          <h2>Partnerships</h2>
          <p>Our drug policy work is strengthened through collaboration with:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Harm reduction coalitions statewide</li>
            <li>Public health departments</li>
            <li>Recovery community organizations</li>
            <li>Medical and treatment providers</li>
            <li>Family advocacy groups</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
